🧠 Practice Questions (Using across() + functions)
🟢 Basic Level (1–6)
1.	Convert all numeric columns to integers using mutate() and across(). 
2.	Round all numeric columns to 2 decimal places. 
3.	Replace all NA values in numeric columns with 0. 
4.	Apply log() transformation to all numeric columns. 
5.	Multiply all numeric columns by 100. 
6.	Convert all character columns to uppercase. 
________________________________________
🟡 Intermediate Level (7–14)
7.	Calculate mean of all numeric columns using summarise(across()). 
8.	Calculate both mean and median for all numeric columns. 
9.	Get standard deviation of all numeric columns grouped by region. 
10.	Count number of NA values in each column. 
11.	Create new columns with suffix _scaled by scaling all numeric columns. 
12.	Apply different functions: 
•	mean for numeric columns 
•	n_distinct for character columns 
13.	Rename all numeric columns by adding prefix "num_". 
14.	Create new columns where: 
•	price → price_log 
•	quantity → quantity_sqrt
using across() selectively. 
________________________________________
🔵 Advanced Level (15–20)
15.	Group by product_category and calculate: 
•	mean 
•	max 
•	min
for all numeric columns. 
16.	Use across() with a custom function:
→ Normalize all numeric columns (min-max scaling). 
17.	Create a summary table where: 
•	numeric columns → mean 
•	character columns → first value 
18.	Apply multiple functions (mean, sd) and control column names using .names. 
19.	Filter rows where any numeric column is greater than 1000 using if_any(). 
20.	Filter rows where all numeric columns are positive using if_all(). 
